Clean v1.0

Syntax: clean [-s] | [-h] | [-d DEST] | [-D] | [-a] | [-A] | [-i] | [-r]

Options:
  -s SHOW       Show the files of the current profile
  -h HIDE       Hide the files of the current profile
  -d DEST       Change the current destination
  -D SHOW DEST  Show the current destination
  -a AUTO CLEAN Enable/disable Auto Clean: show/hide based on the current state
  -A SHOW AUTO  Show if auto clean is enabled/disabled
  -i INFO       Show clean info page (Only really useful when Auto Clean is enabled)
  -r DEFAULTS   Restore Clean to defaults

Clean is a tool to easily show or hide files from a certain directory.
It's recommended to add an alias to Clean in your .bash_profile